The paper introduces a machine learning approach for studying the learnability of relational properties in software design, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Alloy, a software design language, which suggests a potential fit with software engineering (cs.SE) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper employs state-of-the-art approximate and exact model counters, which suggests a potential fit with programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
